      <akn:section eId="sec_19_604_09">
        <akn:num>19-604.09</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Requirements.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_19-604_09_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>Except as provided in subsection (b) of this section, a transfer on death deed shall contain the essential elements and formalities of a properly recordable inter vivos deed.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_19-604_09_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A transfer on death deed shall state that the transfer to the designated beneficiary is to occur at the transferor’s death.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_19-604_09_c">
      <akn:num>(c)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A transfer on death deed shall be recorded before the transferor’s death in the Office of Recorder of Deeds.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
